/** With the use of unit(a), we can now implement a function that takes its array 
* and converts 0 values to 1.
* 
* With our unit vector, we can then proceed to invert our unit vector such that all 0's become 1's, and vice versa. 
* This allows us to add our original array back to itself with only 0's incremented by 1. 
*/
non0(a)
Local a
Func
abs(z\unit(a)-1)+a
EndFunc
